  <section aria-labelledby="why">
    <h2 id="why">Why this exists</h2>
    <p>Population-scale software runs on infrastructure operated by parties with their own incentives. Most governance debates argue about <em>who</em> should hold authority. The framework asks the prior question: <em>what structural properties must hold for any holder of authority to remain correctable?</em> Five of them, the framework argues, and they are testable.</p>
  </section>

